1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
How do I explain this to Jan?

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Um, well, basically it's like a really big party and everybody gets super dressed up

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,000
and there's a bunch of different gods and each of the gods has a special power

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,000
like the Care Bears, you know, except-

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Oh, please stop talking. Three words or less.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
It's like an Indian Halloween.

7
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,000
An Indian Halloween.

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Okay, great.

9
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Tonight, one of our most ethnic coworkers, Kelly, has invited us all to a Dwali celebration

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
put on by her community.

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
What is Dwali, you may ask.

12
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Well, to have Kelly explain it.

13
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:41,000
It's, I have, blah blah blah. It's so super fun and it's gonna be great.

14
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,000
A lot of gods with unpronounceable names.

15
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Twenty minutes later you find out that it's essentially a Hindu Halloween.

16
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Pam, could you put Jan on please?

17
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Michael, you're on with Jan.

18
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Hello, Jan.

19
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Michael, what is this about you letting everyone leave work early today?

20
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Well, I was letting everybody go to the big Diwali party.

21
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
What is Diwali?

22
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,000
What is Diwali? You don't know what Diwali is?

23
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Wow, Jan, I'm surprised.

24
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
It's the Hindu Festival of Lights. I just assumed you'd be familiar with it.

25
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:17,000
It's the most sacred and honored Hindu holiday in the world.

26
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,000
It's like Christmas, Easter and Halloween rolled into one.

27
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,000
I bet you're not even aware that our own Kelly Kapoor, who works in...

28
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Customer service.

29
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Customer service is a Hindu person.

30
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Of course I know Kelly. I thought she was Muslim.

31
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,000
What? I'm not Muslim.

32
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Well, I think it sounds lovely. I think it sounds like a good idea.

33
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
You do?

34
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Yes, of course. It's important to celebrate our company's rich diversity.

35
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:46,000
And in fact, Michael, if you had planned better, we might have been able to charter a bus to the event.

36
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Wow, I didn't know about that.

37
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,000
Or been a sponsor for the party itself.

38
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
For Kelly, that seems a bit much.

39
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Hey, one person is an integral part of the fabric.

40
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,000
She's so wonderful.

41
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Yeah, you should see her naked.

42
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
I had promised Carol a romantic evening on the town.

43
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:11,000
I wanted to take her on this spooky hayride thing, but it was like $70 a person.

44
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,000
And she's allergic to hay.

45
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:17,000
So I said, pop a Claritin and I will spot you the 70 bucks.

46
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:22,000
And he's like, I don't like to borrow money or take unnecessary medication.

47
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:27,000
And I'm like, well, you're really not going to like what I slipped in your drink last night.

48
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,000
And she was like, what the hell are you talking about?

49
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:36,000
I'm like, I'm kidding. I didn't put a roof over your head.

50
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
And we laughed so hard.

51
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:43,000
It was hilarious. Oh.

52
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
So yes, I'm very excited about the Diwali party.

53
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
There we go.

54
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Nice dress, Ryan.

55
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
It's not a dress. It's a kertha.

56
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Okay.

57
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,000
You look so handsome.

58
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
You really do. I love the material.

59
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,000
I know.

60
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
How come you didn't give me one?

61
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
I...

62
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,000
So between Meredith, Minnie Van, and if I borrow Bob's Yukon, that should fit about 12 people.

63
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
I actually might not go.

64
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Feeling kind of tired.

65
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Do you want to make Appletinis and watch Sex and the City at my place?

66
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Oh, I don't know. I haven't decided yet.

67
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:03,000
I know when you break up with someone, you're supposed to be really social, get back out there.

68
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:10,000
I'm just not sure that out there includes the Lackawanna County Hindu American Associations

69
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Family Diwali Celebration at West Scranton High School.

70
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
I don't know why we're going to this. It's not a calendar holiday.
